		   <br><br>
           <h3>Teaching/Research Experience:</h3>
           <p>
		   Prof. Neena Sinha began her academic journey at the Research Institute for Economics and Business Administration, Kobe University, Japan as a Visiting Research Scholar in 1989. Motivated by the culture of academic excellence overseas, she started her teaching career at BITS Pilani in 1992 and moved on to the University School of Management Studies (USMS) as founding faculty at the Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University (GGS IPU), Delhi in 1999 and rose to the post of Professor (Strategic Business) in 2009. Currently she is serving as Professor and Dean USMS, GGS IPU.
</p><p>She has successfully supervised 07 doctoral (Ph.D) theses and completed a few sponsored research projects. She is the Deputy Coordinator of ongoing UGC SAP-DRS Project at USMS. Her current research interests include Corporate Social Responsibility & Sustainable Marketing, Development Informatics and Total Quality Management. She has published over seventy five research papers in management journals and proceedings of International conferences. She has also authored two edited volumes and seven modules of Strategic Management.  
</p><p>In all, she has 24 years of teaching and research experience. During her eighteen years long tenure at the GGS IP University, she has also played vital role in many administrative functions of the University. These include: Director-Development, Coordinator IPU-Intellectual Property Right Cell, Coordinator Indraprastha Internal Quality Assurance Cell and Chief Coordinator Industry Institute Partnership Cell. Her other significant executive roles at the University include coordination of University’s Accreditation by NAAC, Bangalore in 2007 and University’s Re-Accreditation in 2013; working as Management Representative for ISO: 9001: 2008 Certification from the STQC Certification Services, Ministry of Communication and IT, New Delhi; coordinating with the UGC and Formulation of IPR Policy of the University. She has been an Expert member of many UGC Committees including Committee to frame Guidelines of UGC Community College Scheme, UGC Screening Committee for approval of Community College and Bachelor of Vocational Studies (B. Voc.) courses and get regular invitations to serve as an external expert on various Interview Boards. She is a member of Strategic Management Society, USA. 
</p>

